# agentvm profile: OpenClaude
#
# Runs OpenClaude — an open-source coding-agent CLI built on Claude Code's
# codebase but routing to OpenAI / Gemini / GitHub Models / Ollama / OpenRouter
# via OpenAI-compatible APIs. https://github.com/Gitlawb/openclaude
#
# IMPORTANT: OpenClaude uses ~/.claude/ for its config because it shares Claude
# Code's binary surface, but agentvm gives each agent its own HOME so OpenClaude
# agents NEVER touch the host's Claude Code state. We deliberately do not seed
# from the host's ~/.claude/ — only from ~/.openclaude-profile.json, OpenClaude's
# own provider-config file. The setup script bootstraps a clean .claude/ inside
# the agent home with onboarding marked complete, so no wizards appear.
#
# Env vars (OPENAI_API_KEY, OPENAI_BASE_URL, OPENAI_MODEL, CLAUDE_CODE_USE_OPENAI,
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, FIRECRAWL_API_KEY) are inherited from the host shell + ~/.agentvm/env.
#
# Usage:
#   agentvm spawn my-oc --profile openclaude
#   agentvm spawn my-oc --profile openclaude -- openclaude --model gpt-5

PROFILE_LABEL="OpenClaude"

# Default command: openclaude in non-interactive auto-approve mode
PROFILE_CMD="openclaude --dangerously-skip-permissions"

# Read-only: openclaude is typically installed via npm, so the active node
# runtime needs to be reachable inside the sandbox.
PROFILE_RO_PATHS="${HOME}/.local/bin:${HOME}/.nvm:${HOME}/.bun"

# State dirs to seed from $HOME into the per-agent HOME. Note: deliberately
# omitting .claude / .claude.json — OpenClaude is NOT Claude Code and shouldn't
# inherit Claude Code's plugins, sessions, or onboarding state.
PROFILE_STATE_DIRS=".openclaude-profile.json"

# Setup script: writes a minimal .claude/settings.json and .claude.json so
# OpenClaude skips its first-run wizard (theme picker, login chooser, etc.).
PROFILE_POST_CREATE_SCRIPT="$SCRIPT_DIR/profiles/setup-openclaude.sh"
